We shudder to give you the 1961 prices but we do know that many lesser Chateaux cost more in the 1961 market today than the peerless Chateau Haut Brion of 1959 commanded on the same date two years ago.

The prices listed below for the 1959 chateau-bottled Clarets may seem high if you compare them with what you were , paying for the 1955s two years ago, but we must repeat in full sincerity that these very wines cost approxi- mately the same in Bordeaux today on a wholesale trade level that we are quoting you below. We do admit that they are not inexpensive but we must assert that the wines are truly great, are priced here well below the market and will command considerably higher quotations a year from now. Our advice is simple—if you want 1959 Clarets, buy them now or resign yourself to never having the personal pleasure of their fantastic greatness in your wine cellar.
